article.headline: Vermont 84, N.C.-Wilmington 73
article.story: WILMINGTON, N.C. (AP) -- Marqus Blakely had 19 points and 19 rebounds to lead Vermont past North Carolina-Wilmington 84-73 on Saturday night. Five Catamounts scored in double figures in snapping the Seahawks' four-game winning streak and sending them to 0-3 all-time in BracketBuster games. Mike Trimboli had 15 points, Joey Accaoui scored 13, Nick Vier finished with 12 and Kyle Cieplicki added 11 for Vermont (14-13), which shot 50 percent and won its second straight. T.J. Carter had 24 points and 10 rebounds to lead UNC Wilmington (18-11), which entered having won nine of 11 but shot 41 percent and made just 6-of-21 attempts from 3-point range. Vladimir Kuljanin finished with 11 points and Todd Hendley and Daniel Fountain each scored 10 for the Seahawks.
